<div class="well">

	<h3>Where are the bathrooms?</h3>
	<p>There are 4:
	Men's room is directly outside the door from reception, to the left
	Women's room is outside the door from reception, half-way down the hall, in an alcove between the freight and passenger elevators
	Accessible bathroom is adjacent to the Women's room
	A Guest bathroom is located between the Kitchen and the Large Conference Room</p>
	
	<h3>How do I get into the bathrooms?</h3>
	<p>Men: punch code 3-4-5 in on the keypad on the bathroom door handle - voil√°
	Women & Accessible bathrooms: there are keys (for each) at reception, hanging up directly next to the mailboxes for you to use anytime, no permission required from the teacher!</p>
	
	<h3>Oops, I left the key in the bathroom - do I need to break down the door?</h3>
	<p>Not cause to panic - there is more than one key to each bathroom, so you should be able to grab the other key and retrieve the lost one. The other key failing to appear readily, let reception or Amanda know, and a rescue mission will be set in motion.</p>
	
	<h3>I was just in the bathroom (or kitchen), and there was no soap/ paper towels/ toilet paper/ light/ air conditioning/ water/ disco ball/ etc. How does that get fixed?</h3>
	<p>Any and all missing or lacking items and amenities should be reported to reception and Amanda, and we will raise the appropriate alarms to remedy the problem as soon as possible - usually immediately in the case of soap or paper goods.</p>
	
	<h3>What an amazing kitchen, replete with coffee, tea, and sundry beverage items! What is for public consumption?</h3>
	<p>Coffee (generally Peet's), tea (PG Tips), milk (the full range), and an array of sweeteners are all for everyone's enjoyment and use, so caffeinate away!</p>
	
	<h3>I keep seeing this huge array of food and beverages every Monday morning, and people consuming it, and it looks really good; am I allowed to partake?</h3>
	<p>Yes! Every Monday morning (with the exception of major Monday holidays, of course) we lay out a big breakfast spread as a nice welcome back from the weekend for the whole workspace. You (workspace resident or guest of resident) should absolutely join us, meet your neighbors, engage in a little office banter around the pile of bagels or the pot of coffee, and kick off your week the right way. </p>
	
	<h3>How does coffee appear?</h3>
	<p>Everything in the kitchen is a community resource - everyone participates, so everyone can (and should) make more coffee when a pot gets emptied. If you are nervous, uncomfortable or just totally unfamiliar with the process of making a pot of coffee, Amanda will happily host tutorial sessions - just ask! </p>
	
