	<h3>How much of my own stuff can I keep in that small refrigerator? </h3>
	<p>The refrigerator is big enough for us to keep all the milk and breakfast food (for Mondays), as well as for anyone to keep their lunch in there that needs it. Not your lunch for the next 2 weeks, more like that days meal, maybe tomorrows.</p>
	
	<h3>I think I had a batch of vegetables/ fruit/ chili/ greasy leaky leftovers/ unidentifiable food in the fridge at some point in the last 3 weeks, and now I can't find it - where could it have gone?</h3>
	<p>Every Friday, when the groceries arrive for the Monday breakfast, the refrigerator gets thoroughly purged, both in order to make room for that food, as well as to prevent any new life forms from cropping up. Anything that has been in there since the previous Friday goes, unless properly labeled, or that comes with a reliable expiration date.
	</p>
	
	<h3>I have a meeting, how do I get a conference room?</h3>
	<p>First, you need email permission in the google calendars that represent the 3 different conference rooms that we have - 701, the Large "L", and the Small "K" conference rooms. For that, Amanda will invite anyone that needs/ wants access. Once you have that, you can view what is available and when, and reserve the room that you need by simply creating a calendar event within that room's calendar with your group's name in it. Coming soon, a better, unified conference room calendaring system...</p>
	
